        <div id="definition" class="container-fluid bg-danger-subtle mx-auto">
            <div class="m-5">
                <div class="text-dark text-center"> <!--Centered text to look nice with centered carousel-->
                    <h4>Throwing up and blacking out on your periods?</h4>
                    <p> It may be time to consider if you might have endometriosis</p>
                </div>
                <br>
                <div id="definition" class="p-5 mb-8 bg-light rounded-3">
                    <div class="container-fluid py-1">
                        <!--Very proud of this section,
                            made use of different typography commands to make it look like a dictionary entree-->
                        <h1><strong>endometriosis</strong></h1>
                        <code>[ en-doh-mee-tree-oh-sis ]</code>
                        <br><small><i>noun Pathology.</i></small>
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <p>
                            Abnormal tissue growth that can cause <span class="text-danger-emphasis">
                                debilitating pain, heavy bleeding, anxiety, depression, infertility</span> and many
                            other complications. There is no known cure.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                data-bs-target="#collapseExample" aria-controls="collapseExample">
                                Read more
                            </button>
                            <!--Also very proud of this "Read more" button, now people may choose to read more if they are interested
                            and they won't be turned off by huge chunks of text-->
                        </p>
                        <div class="collapse" id="collapseExample">
                            <div class="card-body card-text">
                                <p>
                                    This gynaecological condition occurs when uterus lining tissues grow outside of it,
                                    especially in other pelvic organs such as ovaries.

                                    The exact cause is not yet fully understood, but it is believed to
                                    be related to hormonal imbalances and genetic factors.

                                    The only definitive diagnosis is laparoscopic surgery, as non-invasive methods
                                    are inconclusive.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    For short-term pain alleviation and reduction of the growth of endometrial tissues,
                                    pain medication and hormonal therapies are often used.

                                    However, excision surgery is necessary in order to attempt to sever the roots.
                                    Even then, complete remission is not guaranteed as it may reoccur.
                                </p>
                                <!--Spent lots of time copywriting this so that it looks digestible on small and large screens-->
                                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" type="button" data-bs-toggle="offcanvas"
                                    data-bs-target="#offcanvasExample" aria-controls="offcanvasExample">
                                    Oh shoot that sounds a lot like me...
                                    <!---Incorporated this offcanvas pop up so that it's noticeable and impactful-->
                                </button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
