            <div id="mystory" class="row" style="background-color:lightpink">
                <div class="col-sm-4 col-12 p-5 d-flex align-items-center ">
                    <img src="endo4.png" class="img-fluid img-thumbnail rounded-circle p-3 " alt="portraiture">
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-8 col-12 p-5" style="background-color:lavenderblush">
                    <h1 class="my-3">This is my story</h1>
                    <p> When I was 14, I vomitted when it was the time of the month, the color was <span
                            class="text-danger">red</span> (but I think the colour came from the grapes).</p>
                    <p>When I was 16, I fainted for the first time after explosive diarrhea (sorry, mom).</p>
                    <p>When I was 18, I collapsed in public after a competition, everyone was almost as white as I was
                        (we
                        won though, all good).</p>
                    <p>When I was 21, I was in so much pain I could not talk or walk, I thought I was going to die.</p>
                    <p>When I was 23, I went to see the doctor, they told me <i>"some periods are just more
                            painful"</i>.</p>
                    <p>When I was 24, I had a concussion and blacked out before I could call the ambulance.</p>
                    <p>When I was 25, I called the ambulance.</p>
                    <p>When I was 26, I was prescribed with pills, had ultra sounds, MRI scans, and inserted a mirena
                        coil.
                    </p>
                    <p>I am 27 now, and it still hurts.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
